McGuire later proposed 12 steps in 1989 to explain the factors that influence behaviorBehavior, including:
Contact informationInformation;
Pay attention to the informationInformation;
Like or become interested in the informationInformation;
Understanding the message (what can be learnedLearned?);
Skill acquisition (learn how to operate);
Convincing message (change of attitudeAttitude);
Storage/consent of memory contentsContent;
InformationInformation search and retrieval;
Making decisionsDecision based on retrieval;
The behaviorBehavior is consistent with decisionDecision-making;
Strengthen ideal behaviorBehavior;
Strengthening after behaviorBehavior.
